{"questionId":"32450633","questionHtml":"<p>Solve the differential equation <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>L</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>k</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><msub><mi>L</mi><mo>∞</mo></msub><mo>-</mo><mi>L</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>, using the initial condition. Write your answer in the form <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>L</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>f</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mi>t</mi></mfenced></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempt to separate variables&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>∫</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><msub><mi>L</mi><mo>∞</mo></msub><mo>-</mo><mi>L</mi></mrow></mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>L</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>∫</mo><mi>k</mi><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>t</mi></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mrow><msub><mi>L</mi><mo>∞</mo></msub><mo>-</mo><mi>L</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>k</mi><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for correct integration of RHS including “<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi></math>” <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for correct integration of LHS. Accept absence of absolute value, since <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>L</mi><mo>∞</mo></msub><mo>-</mo><mi>L</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>attempt to remove ln using e&nbsp;from their integrated equation&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>L</mi><mo>∞</mo></msub><mo>-</mo><mi>L</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>k</mi><mi>t</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>c</mi></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mi>A</mi><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>k</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></msup></math></strong></em></p>\n<p>substitute initial conditions into their integrated equation, to find constant of integration&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>L</mi><mo>∞</mo></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>L</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo mathvariant=\"italic\">-</mo><mi>c</mi></mrow></msup><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mi>A</mi></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> The previous two marks may be seen in either order.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>L</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>L</mi><mo>∞</mo></msub><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><msub><mi>L</mi><mo>∞</mo></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>L</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mrow></mfenced><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo mathvariant=\"italic\">-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">k</mi><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">t</mi></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[6 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"32450633","referenceCode":"24N.3.AHL.TZ0.2h","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Solve the differential equation dLdt=k L∞-L, using the initial condition. Write your answer in the form L=f t.","paper":"3","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"h","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 6]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","AHL 5.14—Setting up a DE, solve by separating variables"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}